    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1501</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-22T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 24, 4.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2919. Person referred to in my 2769, March 4,<note n="1" xml:id="d109fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_147">p. 147</ref>.</note>
                    contemplates returning home in a few days. Is there any message the Department
                    desires to have intimated to him unofficially?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
